<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EACFF2248A752B1FE0CF909" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EACFF2248A752B1FD6AF925" blockId="226.[151,1438,1437,1930]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EACFF2248A752B1FE29FA45" bold="true" box="[151,396,1437,1462]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EACFF224ABD52B1FD43FA45" box="[653,742,1437,1461]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; petiole testaceous; legs testaceous, except coxae and profemur brown. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 9:6:6:8:8:8:7.5:7:6:8. Head dull, completely reticulate rugose; frontal line complete; occipital carina complete; POL = 3; OL = 2; OOL = 6.5; OPL = 6; TL = 6. Scutum dull, reticulate rugose. Notauli absent. Scutellum shiny, smooth, unsculptured, slightly granulated near anterior margin. Metanotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Propodeum reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two longitudinal keels, lateral areas rugose and median area smooth, unsculptured. Fore wing with 2 dark transverse bands; stigmal vein with distal part shorter than proximal part (18:21). Petiole very long. Metasoma about three times as long as petiole (34:10). Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EACFF2248F751CDFE0CF909" blockId="226.[151,1438,1437,1930]" box="[199,425,1761,1785]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EACFF2248F751CDFE80F909" bold="true" box="[199,293,1761,1785]" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
